HOW TO USE
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
{% if benchmark.platform_family == "linux" %}
1. Copy this entire folder to the target Linux machine
2. Open a terminal with root/sudo privileges
3. Run: sudo bash {{ script_filename }}
4. Wait for the audit to complete
5. Collect the results/ directory
6. Import results/audit_results.json back into AuditForge
{% elif benchmark.platform_family == "windows" %}
1. Copy this entire folder to the target Windows machine
2. Open PowerShell as Administrator
3. Run: powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File {{ script_filename }}
4. Wait for the audit to complete
5. Collect the results\ directory
6. Import results\audit_results.json back into AuditForge
{% elif benchmark.platform_family == "database" %}
1. Copy this entire folder to a machine with database client tools
2. Connect to the target database server
3. Execute the SQL script:
{% if "postgresql" in benchmark.platform|lower %}
   psql -U postgres -f {{ script_filename }} -o results/audit_output.txt
{% elif "oracle" in benchmark.platform|lower %}
   sqlplus / as sysdba @{{ script_filename }}
{% elif "mssql" in benchmark.platform|lower or "sql server" in benchmark.platform|lower %}
   sqlcmd -S server -i {{ script_filename }} -o results\audit_output.txt
{% else %}
   Use your database client to execute {{ script_filename }}
{% endif %}
4. Collect the results/ directory
5. Import the output back into AuditForge
{% elif benchmark.platform_family == "network" %}
1. SSH into the target network device
2. Enter privileged EXEC mode (e.g., enable)
3. Set terminal length to 0
4. Start logging your terminal session
5. Paste the commands from {{ script_filename }} into the session
6. Save the terminal log as results/audit_output.txt
7. Import the output back into AuditForge
{% else %}
1. Review the commands in {{ script_filename }}
2. Execute each command on the target system
3. Record all outputs
4. Import results back into AuditForge
{% endif %}

══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PACKAGE CONTENTS
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

{{ script_filename }}     — Main audit script/commands
rules_reference.json      — JSON list of rules being checked
README.txt                — This file
results/                  — Directory for audit results (created during execution)

══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
IMPORTANT NOTES
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

- This script is READ-ONLY: it will NOT modify the target system
- Each command's output is saved as evidence in results/raw_outputs/
- If a command fails, the script continues with the next rule
- Running the script multiple times produces the same results
- Results are saved in machine-readable JSON format

